title: Cardinal Newman ready to tee it up in state championship
text:
Cardinal Newman ready to tee it up in state championship 
By Matt Lincoln/CBS12WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (CBS12) - South Florida is the best place to play golf in the country, so it should come as no surprise that the best high school golf teams hail from Palm Beach County. Qualifying out of this region to get States is not an easy task.But Cardinal Newman has done it now 6 of the last 8 years. The Crusaders advanced along with King's Academy, but they had to sweat it out. Newman topped third place Benjamin by just one stroke - the Crusaders needed birdies from Jeffrey Cunningham and Andre Wade on their final holes to survive. Now they head back to states for the first time in two seasons, when they finished sixth overall. That year, the moment was a little too big for them, and they started out slow, but this year they're ready to bring some hardware back.The State Championship tournament starts Tuesday, at Mission Hills, west of Orlando.
